A Django project that can be pushed to OpenShift,

Django Admin (superuser) account in SQLite database
===========

Username: admin
Password: adminpass

Repo layout
===========

wsgi/ - Externally exposed wsgi code
web/ - Django project which sets up root URLs
bikesurvey/ - Simple Django app, replace with your code
libs/ - Additional libraries
setup.py - Standard setup.py for OpenShift
.openshift/action_hooks/pre_build - Script that gets run every git push before the build
.openshift/action_hooks/build - Script that gets run every git push as part of the build process (on the CI system if available)
.openshift/action_hooks/deploy - Script that gets run every git push after build but before the app is restarted
.openshift/action_hooks/post_deploy - Script that gets run every git push after the app is restarted

Note about setup.py
====================

Dependencies in install_requires will be installed during git push.